{
  "texts": [
    "We have highlighted in section 2.4 two possible interpretations of the Wakimoto free field description [41] of the theory at k = 1; either as a theory in which the worldsheet is pinned to the boundary, or as a free field realisation along the lines of that proposed in [50].",
    "There are pros and cons to each perspective.",
    "In the Φ → ∞ limit, it is unclear to what extent this theory really describes the full physics on AdS 3 as the interaction term will be absent.",
    "Indeed, a connection to the full AdS 3 sigma model requires the inclusion of this interaction term, which renders β and β as Lagrange multipliers rather than dynamical fields.",
    "Conversely, whilst the free field approach akin to [50] certainly describes the full AdS 3 sigma model, the details of how the theory simultaneously encodes the degrees of freedom of the holomorphic and antiholomorphic sectors is unclear."
  ]
}